{
  "texts": [
    "An LLM is not born into a society, it is born into a body of text.",
    "An LLM is, however, so good at outputting text that this is not apparent to the consumer.",
    "The consequence is that the problem will no longer be how we socialise the machines but how the machines socialise us: how, unnoticeably, they will align our values with theirs, which, we have seen, are either no values or the values of their hidden controllers.",
    "What we should expect is already evident in the way social media affects the definition of groups in society.",
    "24 The human-like plausibility of LLM's will move this transformation further and faster."
  ]
}